			<description><![CDATA[<p>
Bishops Services Inc., a wholly owned subsidiary of Sterling InfoSystems Inc., is a 114 year old Business Due Diligence and Background Investigation firm.&nbsp; Bishops works with financial services, legal and corporate organizations to assist with their domestic and international due diligence needs relating to investments, M&amp;A transactions, partnerships and senior level hiring.&nbsp;<br />
This position, based out of the NYC Headquarters, has primary responsibility for new client development in the financial services sector, particularly in the alternative investment space.&nbsp; Qualified candidates should have a proven history of success at new business development within the financial services sector.</p>
<p>
<br />
Job Duties/ Responsibilities<br />
&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Meet monthly/quarterly/annual sales quotas and other metrics<br />
&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Build and manage new business relationships throughout the sales cycle to gain new accounts in an assigned territory<br />
&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Review and analyze market data to develop and implement own business plan and utilize company resources to maximize sales effectiveness<br />
&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Assess potential of prospects and develop strategies and presentations accordingly<br />
&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Understand prospects&rsquo; organizational dynamics and probe to discover needs and key decision makers<br />
&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Perform analysis of prospects&rsquo; business processes and design solutions that best meet customer requirements<br />
&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Articulate complex concepts and business solutions clearly through demonstrations and proposals<br />
&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Coordinate processes with internal, external and/or third parties when necessary<br />
&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Participate in regular structured sales and business training programs to improve sales performance</p>
<p>
Skills/ Knowledge<br />
&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Successful record of new client development within the financial services vertical, particularly into the alternative investment space (including proposals, presentations and complex/ lengthy sales cycles)<br />
&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Strong desire to succeed and ability to work independently and as part of a team<br />
&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Effectively communicate with senior level decision makers in organizations worldwide<br />
&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Aggressive attitude in developing new accounts and building personal relationships<br />
&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Excellent presentation, written, and verbal skills<br />
&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Ability to create and deliver convincing arguments covering a broad range of complex issues<br />
&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Employ a consultative, customer-focused selling approach<br />
&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Superior time management skills and strong attention to detail<br />
&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Effectively handle objections and demonstrate negotiation skills</p>
<p>
Experience Levels<br />
&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; 4+ years of sales experience with a demonstrated history of sales success, consistent overachievement of quota and revenue goals, and accomplishment in prior positions<br />
&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Four year degree from an accredited university</p>
