			<description><![CDATA[<p>
Job Overview</p>
<p>
Sterling Infosystems is the largest pure play international background screening company. A differentiator to our customer value proposition is the strategic resources that work directly with our customers to ensure their success.&nbsp;&nbsp; For Sterling, our relationship managers are critical to the growth of our business.</p>
<p>
As a Relationship Manager you will be responsible for full end to end customer account management.&nbsp; The successful Relationship Manager not only manages the day to day screening program for the customer, he/she develops strategic relationships deep and wide within the customer, identifies opportunities to expand Sterling&rsquo;s footprint within the customer via incremental products and services.&nbsp;&nbsp;<br />
<br />
Job Duties/ Responsibilities<br />
&bull; Implement and manage customer background screening programs to best align with customer&rsquo;s organizational needs and goals<br />
&bull; Structure and implement long term contract/agreements with customers to renew and grow revenue from customer base<br />
&bull; Understand each client&rsquo;s organizational dynamics and probe to discover model and core initiatives in a solutions sales capacity and assist client in goal achievement by leveraging Sterling&rsquo;s suite of products and services<br />
&bull; Identify and develop multi-level relationships with key decision makers and decision influencers to ensure retention and relationship stability regardless of client&rsquo;s turnover in key roles.&nbsp; (3 x 3)<br />
&bull; Create strategic account plan as a roadmap to grow customer revenue and deliver world class customer satisfaction<br />
&bull; Liaise between client, internal departments and partners to provide clear and accurate program guidance for customers<br />
&bull; Conduct regular business reviews using value add propositions to mitigate client risk and enhance background screening programs&nbsp;<br />
&bull; Grow customer book of business to target vs. prior year</p>
<p>
Qualifications and Requirements<br />
&bull; Highly motivated Account Executive with proven ability to drive results<br />
&bull; 7-10 years of Account Management and Account Executive experience working with all levels within Human Resource departments<br />
&bull; Sales experience a plus<br />
&bull; Superior written and in person communication skills at senior levels of the customer<br />
&bull; Superior program management, presentation and organizational skills.<br />
&bull; Proven track record in maintain long-terming business partnerships with clients<br />
&bull; Prior industry experience in retail, healthcare, staffing&nbsp; and financial services are plus<br />
&bull; Proficient in using CRM platform, Salesforce.com experience preferred<br />
&bull; Bachelor&rsquo;s Degree required, graduate degree a plus<br />
<br />
Statement of Other Duties<br />
This document describes the major duties, responsibilities, and authorities of this job, and is not intended to be a complete list of all tasks and functions.&nbsp; It should be understood, therefore, that incumbents may be asked to perform job-related duties beyond those explicitly described.<br />
&nbsp;</p>
